To this end, we use the algorithm in [19] (denoted by \(\mathsf{OptimalOja}\), see Proposition A.5.3) for subgaussian data, which uses an iteration-dependent sequence of step-sizes \(\left\{\eta_{i}\right\}_{i\in\left[n\right]}\). We run Algorithm 2 with \(\mathsf{OptimalOja}\) as the procedure to do sparse PCA. This leads to the minimax error rate, shown in Theorem 3.7. The high probability bounds in Theorem 3.5 and 3.7 both use the support recovery guarantees derived in Section 3.1 and the boosting procedure described in Section 3.4. Detailed proofs for both results can be found in Appendix Section A.5.

